  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Inspect Honda Smart lock/unlock switch"
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Wear gloves when working."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Work must be performed so as not to damage the door panel, tailgate, and any parts to be removed."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Front door lining removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000720",
          "label": "Front door lining removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Front door hole seal removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "942_3.0_jpn_11580748_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the plug cap (A). Disconnect the coupler (B). Remove the harness clip (C). Remove the front door hole seal (D) as required. If the front door hall seal is damaged or torn, replace it with a new front door hall seal."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Front door outer handles Lock/unlock switch Check"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "942_3.0_jpn_11580749_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "942_3.0_jpn_11580750_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Disconnect the coupler (A). Inspect the continuity between terminals in each position of the coupler (B) and confirm that there is continuity only between ○ and ○. If there is no continuity, the front door outer handle lock/unlock switch is defective, Replace the front door outer handle. Connect the coupler.",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000721",
          "label": "Replace the front door outer handle.",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Installation Precautions"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Installation is the reverse of the removal procedure."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Tailgate lower lining removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000762",
          "label": "Tailgate lower lining removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Tailgate lock/unlock switch Check"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "942_3.0_jpn_11580751_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "942_3.0_jpn_11580752_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Disconnect the coupler (A). Inspect the continuity between terminals in each position of the coupler (B) and confirm that there is continuity only between ○ and ○. If there is no continuity, the tailgate lock/unlock switch is defective, Replace the tailgate lock/unlock switch. Connect the coupler.",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000943",
          "label": "Replace the tailgate lock/unlock switch.",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
